TY  - JOUR
AU  - Conlisk, John
T1  - An Aggregate Model of Technical Change*
PY  - 1989
Y1  - 1989/11/01
DO  - 10.2307/2937868
JO  - The Quarterly Journal of Economics
JA  - Q J Econ
VL  - 104
IS  - 4
SP  - 787
EP  - 821
SN  - 0033-5533
AB  - A simple aggregate growth model is presented in which technology is described by a probability distribution from which new plants are drawn. Especially good draws are viewed as technological innovations that shift the mean of the following period's plant distribution function. The resulting technical change is endogenous, random, and cumulative. In contrast to conventional growth models, the model's growth path displays nonstationary drift rather than deterministic trend, and the long-run per capita growth rate has positive rather than zero sensitivity to the model's saving parameter.
Y2  - 3/25/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.2307/2937868
ER  - 



